      "side": 1,
      "message": "The reason for this is that we don\u0027t want to add \"build\" to the .gitignore file, since that will potentially ignore a valid user directory named \"build\", say src/com/gradle/tools/build/...    And unfortunately, build isn\u0027t at the root directory, so we can\u0027t just use \"/build\". So, what we do is put all the ignore rules in .gitignore at the root of the project, and then add a .gitignore file in each module where we just suppress /build/.  The alternative was to put some hack like /*/build in the root .gitignore, but that won\u0027t work if modules are nested further down etc, and filtering build/ correctly is pretty important.",
